That means a low of 216ish and a high of 243ish (our nominal voltage is 230v). Well not too long after updating the service I started getting messages about voltage of 215v and lower.. down to about 211.

It got so noisy (with messages) I expanded the range to stop the alerts.

And not in the way you're probably thinking dear reader. The code was fine. The service worked. The alerts came through.

No the issue I've found is: NZ's (or at least my house) power supply is filthy.

The AI had correctly allowed for a 6% variation on our voltage (230).

Timezone was off - so got it to correct that.

Decided to expand the requirements. Asked it to check the incoming voltage and alert when it was outside of expected norms for NZ. It did this right away and was easy to update.

And this is where things got _really_ interesting....

Cliccando, scrivendo, navigando tra finestre e interfacce grafiche. Non si connette via API: si comporta come un umano davanti a un monitor. È il primo sistema operativo pensato per agenti artificiali, non per utenti.
